data.description: 2021 construction with a full acre has been elusive until now! Take advantage of an assumable VA loan with an interest rate under 3.00% Amenities only begin with a private next gen in-law suite, a full acre with space for RV & boat parking, pet grooming station, solar panels and flawless custom upgrades. This epic and sprawling acre property provides a uniquely private and secluded setting within Cabernet. A modern sanctuary with dramatic mountain views in a premier location, this is a very rare offering. No stone has been left unturned to create the masterpiece of Cabernet. Entryway provides access to both the main home and the next gen in-law suite. Throughout the entire home you will find Luxury Vinyl Plank flooring and cordless honey comb top down bottom up blinds. The floorplan is highly functional and flows perfectly from space to space. Tankless water heater and solar system add to the efficiency of the home. Upon entry to the main home you will first be met with a spacious great room. The well appointed kitchen features sealed granite counter tops, a large island and a new Samsung refrigerator. Custom entertainment center boasts soft closing cabinets, drawers and has built in outlets with space for all routers, cords and consoles. The dining area cabinet have under cabinet lighting and a leather finished granite counter top. Around the corner discover the laundry room and fully equipped pet grooming station with additional built in storage space. On the other side of the home, the primary suite has amazing mountain views and a large walk in closet with motion detector lighting. Down the hall, a bedroom with mountain views and another bedroom with a custom closet and built in desk await you. The next gen in- law suite can be accessed from the front entry way, hallway and from its own custom back door for totally private access. Outside, the large backyard has been divided into two separate yard spaces. Multiple gates allow for easy access to and from each yard. The primary backyard features pavers, turf and a large patio cover. French drains and gutters have been installed around the entire exterior of the home. The east side of the secondary backyard features access and space for multiple RV's and boats. Additionally there is an extended irrigation drip line along the back fence and an extended gas line. There is potential and space for your future ideas and projects. The west side of the secondary backyard features another large patio cover with breathtaking mountain views. The south eastern fence was moved up closer to the street in order to create even more space and privacy, a gate was also installed to allow easy access to the street and to create private access to the next gen in-law suite.
